        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 3:18PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 312 PM MDT, locally heavy snow showers were impacting the West
Yellowstone area with reduced visibility, minor accumulations, and
occasional lightning.

HAZARD...Reduced visibility below a half mile.

SOURCE...Trained spotter.

IMPACT...Highly variable visibility.

Locations impacted include...
West Yellowstone and Yellowstone Village.
</description>
        <instruction>Cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these snow showers.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
